# Optional Lé Vibe build hook — copy to `build-env.sh` beside this file to enable **after** defaults (H6 / STEP 14).
# `packaging/scripts/ci-vscodium-linux-dev-build.sh` (CI `linux_compile`, local full compile):
#   1) merges `product-branding-merge.json` into `editor/vscodium/product.json`;
#   2) patches `dev/build.sh` so APP_NAME / ORG_NAME / … honor `${VAR:-upstream}`;
#   3) sources `build-env.lvibe-defaults.sh` (PRODUCT_SPEC §7.3 — committed Lé Vibe names);
#   4) sources this file as `build-env.sh` if present (local overrides).
# Uses `set -a` when sourced so assignments export to the child shell.
#
# Upstream defaults are still defined at the top of `editor/vscodium/dev/build.sh` (verify after submodule bump):
#   APP_NAME, ASSETS_REPOSITORY, BINARY_NAME, CI_BUILD, GH_REPO_PATH, ORG_NAME, SHOULD_BUILD,
#   SKIP_ASSETS, SKIP_BUILD, SKIP_SOURCE, VSCODE_LATEST, VSCODE_QUALITY, VSCODE_SKIP_NODE_VERSION_CHECK
#
# Material identity beyond §7.3 still uses `docs/PRODUCT_SPEC.md` §7.2 — halt with `USER RESPONSE REQUIRED`
# when specs do not decide.
#
# Example — local overrides (uncomment when needed; defaults already set APP_NAME to Lé Vibe):
# export SKIP_ASSETS="no"
